UsenetSharp
  https://github.com/nzbdav-dev/UsenetSharp
  Commit: ccc5de1b114c0b0dc7dae0c933a10a2b99562cac
  License: MIT (same license text as nzbdav above, Copyright (c) 2025 nzbdav-dev)

  Ported components (server/src/Streamarr.Usenet): NNTP protocol connection
  (connect/TLS/AUTHINFO/STAT/HEAD/BODY/ARTICLE/DATE, dot-unstuffing body
  pipe), yEnc header parsing and stream scaffolding (the native RapidYenc
  decoder was replaced with a managed yEnc decoder written for Streamarr),
  read-only stream base classes, and the async semaphore.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Radarr
  https://github.com/Radarr/Radarr
  Commit: c7cf91c14ac42096a013e1bbb1875bd73b6c509f
  License: GPL-3.0

  Ported components (server/src/Streamarr.Core/Parser): the release-name parser
  regexes and logic — QualityParser (resolution / source / video-codec / remux /
  edition / PROPER-REPACK), LanguageParser (language regexes, adapted to emit
  ISO 639-1 codes plus multi / dual-audio flags), ReleaseGroupParser, the
  RegexReplace helper, and the ParserCommon site-prefix / torrent-suffix cleanup
  passes. Each ported file carries a per-file attribution header naming the
  source path and commit. The HDR-flavor and audio codec/channel parsers are
  Streamarr-original.

  Ported components (server/src/Streamarr.Core/Ranking): QualityDefinitions
  adapts Radarr's default quality-definition weights (Qualities/Quality.cs) and
  per-quality size limits (Qualities/QualityDefinition.cs) into decomposed
  resolution / source / audio tiers and bytes-per-minute size bands used by the
  ranker and the size-sanity rejection rule. The rejection engine and
  weighted-sum ranker themselves are Streamarr-original.

Sonarr
  https://github.com/Sonarr/Sonarr
  Commit: f9e18a7c4475345f325237670d7e71ceac97038b
  License: GPL-3.0

  Ported components (server/src/Streamarr.Core/Parser): the episode-parsing
  regexes in EpisodeParser (SxxEyy single + multi, 4-digit seasons, season packs,
  multi-season packs, daily-date, and absolute / anime numbering), plus the
  LanguageParser regexes (shared with Radarr). Each ported file carries a
  per-file attribution header.

